"title": "6115: blame",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6115: blame",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The state of having been accused, correctly or incorrectly, of doing something wrong. Guilt is felt as a result of having been justly blamed for a crime or wrong against a person. Scripture portrays blaming others as a natural human reaction to events. Blame may often be apportioned by people on the basis of a misunderstanding, whereas God's blame of people is just. Christians should seek to lead blameless lives.</p>\n<h2>Blaming others: a basic human characteristic since the fall</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:12-Gen3:13\">GEN 3:12–3:13</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:5\">NUM 20:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num21:5\">NUM 21:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh22:15-Josh22:18\">JOS 22:15–22:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam22:13-1Sam22:15\">1SA 22:13–22:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:8\">2SA 3:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:17-1Kgs18:18\">1KI 18:17–18:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:4-Neh5:5\">NEH 5:4–5:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job4:5-Job4:7\">JOB 4:5–4:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job8:6\">JOB 8:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job11:14-Job11:15\">JOB 11:14–11:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer38:4\">JER 38:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:1-John9:2\">JHN 9:1–9:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:21\">JHN 11:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:1\">ACT 6:1</a></p>\n<h2>Blaming God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer15:16-Jer15:18\">JER 15:16–15:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job2:9\">JOB 2:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job3:23\">JOB 3:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps13:1-Ps13:2\">PSA 13:1–13:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:1-Ps22:2\">PSA 22:1–22:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:9-Ps44:26\">PSA 44:9–44:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps60:1-Ps60:3\">PSA 60:1–60:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:1-Ps74:23\">PSA 74:1–74:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps79:1-Ps79:5\">PSA 79:1–79:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:27\">ISA 40:27</a></p>\n<h2>God justly blames his people for their sins</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:8\">HEB 8:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:19\">ROM 9:19</a></p>\n<h2>Warnings about falsely attributing blame</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:30\">PRO 3:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps71:13\">PSA 71:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps109:18-Ps109:20\">PSA 109:18–109:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps109:29\">PSA 109:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:1-Rom14:4\">ROM 14:1–14:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:7\">ROM 15:7</a></p>\n<h2>Dealing with blame</h2>\n<h3>By confession</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:5\">PSA 32:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:3-Ps51:7\">PSA 51:3–51:7</a></p>\n<h3>By forgiveness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:34\">LUK 23:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:19-Gen50:21\">GEN 50:19–50:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:31-Eph4:32\">EPH 4:31–4:32</a></p>\n<h3>By correcting misunderstandings</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh22:13-Josh22:34\">JOS 22:13–22:34</a></p>\n<h2>God's people should deal gently with those who deserve blame</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:15\">MAT 18:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:19-Jas5:20\">JAS 5:19–5:20</a></p>\n<h2>God's people should aim to live free from blame</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:9-Phil1:10\">PHP 1:9–1:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:1\">GEN 17:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:13\">PSA 19:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:8\">1CO 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:15\">PHP 2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess3:13\">1TH 3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:23\">1TH 5:23</a></p>",
